article.headline: Boston U. 68, St. Bonaventure 57
article.story: BOSTON (AP) -- Corey Lowe matched his career high with 28 points Friday night, leading Boston University to a 68-57 season-opening victory over St. Bonaventure. Lowe, coming off arthroscopic knee surgery in August, started slowly but scored 16 after the half to lead BU to its first season-opening victory since 2001. The sophomore guard also had six rebounds, three of BU?s 10 steals and two assists, finished 8-for-19 from the field, 6-for-16 from 3-point range. He scored 28 points in a 74-65 BU win over Manhattan, his fifth college game, on Nov. 25, 2006. The Terriers trailed 32-26 at the half but used a 14-0 run to establish control and defeat new St. Bonaventure coach Mark Schmidt in his first game. Senior Michael Lee led St. Bonaventure, which turned the ball over 20 times, with 24 points and eight rebounds. Tyler Benson added 10 points. Freshman John Holland scored 12 points in his college debut for the Terriers. Sophomore Carlos Strong added 11 points, seven rebounds and five assists for BU, playing without key starter Tyler Morris. Morris is out indefinitely with a stress reaction in his right leg. BU was just 3-for-18 from 3-point range in the first half but went 6-for-15 from behind the arc after halftime.
